			<div class="textwidget"><p>This blog investigates the relationship between the Internet and public policy. It covers work by the <a href="http://www.oii.ox.ac.uk/">Oxford Internet Institute</a>, and work published in its journal Policy &amp; Internet (Wiley-Blackwell).</p>
<p><img src="http://blogs.oii.ox.ac.uk/policy/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/cover.gif" class="alignleft" alt="Policy and Internet journal" /><a href="http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/journal/10.1002/(ISSN)1944-2866/" onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'outbound-widget', 'http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/journal/10.1002/(ISSN)1944-2866/', 'Policy &amp; Internet']);" >Policy &amp; Internet</a> calls for papers that present genuinely new approaches to policy questions or problems relating to the Internet and related ICTs. Ed-in-Chief: Helen Margetts. <a href="http://mc.manuscriptcentral.com/POI" onclick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'outbound-widget', 'http://mc.manuscriptcentral.com/POI', 'Submit your paper']);" >Submit your paper</a>.<br />
